    "sections": [
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Introduction",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.1",
            "summary": "This supervisory statement is addressed to third-country insurance undertakings that are headquartered outside of the UK or Gibraltar, and have a UK branch (third-country branch undertakings). This in",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.2",
            "summary": "This statement does not apply to Swiss General Insurers, as defined in the PRA Rulebook, to which different requirements apply pursuant to the Swiss Treaty Agreement (No. 91/370/EEC).",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.3",
            "summary": "[Deleted].",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.4",
            "summary": "[Deleted].",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.5",
            "summary": "[Deleted].",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.6",
            "summary": "Firms should also refer to:",
            "as_at_date": ""
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.7",
            "summary": "[Deleted]",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.8",
            "summary": "Other supervisory statements apply to third-country branch undertakings with any necessary modifications, and insofar as they are relevant to rules referred to in the [Third Country Branches Part](/pr",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Compliance with the Guidelines",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "2.1",
            "summary": "The PRA expects third-country branch undertakings to comply with the Branch Guidelines6 that are relevant to them.",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "2.2",
            "summary": "The PRA also expects third-country undertakings that have a third-country pure reinsurance branch to comply with the Branch Guidelines that are relevant to them as if the scope extended to them.",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "2.3",
            "summary": "[Deleted]",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Availability of assets and winding up",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.1",
            "summary": "[Deleted].",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.2",
            "summary": "This text has been moved to [4.1A].",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.3",
            "summary": "The PRA expects considerable importance to be attached to calculating branch assets so as to ensure that only those assets that are available to pay the claims of branch policyholders in the event of ",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.4",
            "summary": "In accordance with Article 49 of Chapter 2A of the Reporting Part of the PRA Rulebook, third-country branch undertakings are required to submit",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.4A",
            "summary": "As part of the analysis referred to in paragraph 3.4, the PRA expects third-country b",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.4B",
            "summary": "As set out in section 6 of this supervisory statement, where there is a significant c",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.5",
            "summary": "[Deleted]",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Worldwide financial resources",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "4.1",
            "summary": "In the PRA Rulebook, Third Country Branches 13 requires a third-country branch undertaking to maintain adequate worldwide financia",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "4.1A",
            "summary": "The PRA expects third-country branch undertakings to maintain financial soundness to ensure that the branch policyholders enjoy the same level of protection as those policyholders of an insurance unde",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "4.2",
            "summary": "The PRA expects the third-country branch undertaking to provide sufficient information so that the PRA may form an opinion on the adequacy of the worldwide financial resources of the undertaking.",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "4.3",
            "summary": "Where the PRA assesses the home jurisdiction’s regime to be broadly equivalent to the regime applied by the PRA to (re)insurers whose head office is in the UK, then compliance with the financial resou",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "4.4",
            "summary": "Where that prudential regime is not broadly equivalent to the regime applied by the PRA to (re)insurers whose head office is in the UK and a third-country branch undertaking from such a jurisdiction n",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "4.5",
            "summary": "Where the adequacy of worldwide financial resources of the third-country branch undertaking is found to be in contravention of the home jurisdiction’s prudential regime, the PRA would expect further i",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "4.6",
            "summary": "As a minimum, the PRA would expect the third-country branch undertaking to submit a realistic plan to recover sufficient financial resources which explicitly identifies any branch specific recovery co",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Scheme of operations",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "5.1",
            "summary": "The PRA will ask for a scheme of operations that sets out all the information required under Third Country Branches 5.1 as part of",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Reporting",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "6.1",
            "summary": "[Deleted]",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "6.2",
            "summary": "[Deleted]",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "6.3",
            "summary": "[Deleted]",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "6.4",
            "summary": "[Deleted]",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "6.5",
            "summary": "[Deleted].",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "6.6",
            "summary": "[Deleted]",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "6.7",
            "summary": "The branch assets which may be included in the reporting templates depend upon the analysis of how available assets would be distributed in a winding up. This is relevant where the winding up regime a",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "6.7A",
            "summary": "The PRA expects that third-country branch undertakings guarantee that branch insurance policyholders can obtain any publicly disclosed information concerning the solvency and financial condition of th",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "6.8",
            "summary": "[Deleted].",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "6.8A",
            "summary": "With regard to branch operations, the PRA expects third-country branch undertakings to submit the following information to the PRA and agree with their supervisor the frequency with which the informat",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "6.8B",
            "summary": "The PRA may also require third-country branch undertakings to communicate any other information prepared under the responsibility of, or at the request of, the administrative, management or supervisor",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "6.8C",
            "summary": "Where a significant development affects the information received from a third-country branch undertaking, the PRA expects that the undertaking should submit an update of this information to the PRA as",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "6.9",
            "summary": "Third-country branches should refer to Supervisory Statement 40/15, ‘Solvency II: reporting and disclosure’.7 The supervisory statement sets out the PRA’s expectations in the following areas that are ",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "6.9A",
            "summary": "Third-country branches should refer to ‘PRA Statement of Policy: Solvency II regulatory reporting waivers’ which specifies the PRA’s approach to waiving submission of certain Solvency II reporting req",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "6.10",
            "summary": "[Deleted]",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
