        "chapter_title": "Application of other supervisory statements to third-country branch undertakings",
        "paragraphs": []
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Own Risk and Solvency Assessment (‘ORSA’) reporting",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "9.1",
            "summary": "Third-country branches are required to submit ORSAs to the PRA.11 Third-country branches should discuss their approach to ORSA submission with their supervisor. The PRA will adopt a proportionate appr",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "9.2",
            "summary": "The PRA expects that third-country branches consider the relative size of the third-country branch, as compared with the third-country branch undertaking, when determining what would constitute a prop",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "9.3",
            "summary": "The PRA expects that where the third-country branch undertaking ORSA is submitted in lieu of a third-country branch ORSA, it should contain the following at minimum, and that additional content should",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "9.4",
            "summary": "Where a third-country branch chooses to submit a branch-specific ORSA, the PRA expects that it should also cover the factors outlined above.",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "9.5",
            "summary": "The PRA expects that as part of its ORSA, the third-country branch undertaking assesses the permanent availability of the branch assets, as set out in paragraph [3.3](/guidance/supervisory-statements/",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "System of governance",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "10.1",
            "summary": "Third-country branches are required to have in place an effective system of governance which provides for sound and prudent management of the business. The detailed requirements on system of governanc",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "10.2",
            "summary": "The PRA expects third-country branches to assess how their organisational structures support transparency, accountability, and the need for appropriate management of any conflicts of interest, includi",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "The Senior Managers & Certification Regime (SM&CR)",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "11.1",
            "summary": "All third-country branches are required to have a fit and proper individual appointed as the Senior Management Function (SMF) 19 – Head of Third Country Branch (and, where relevant, a With-Profits Act",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "11.2",
            "summary": "The PRA expects third-country branch undertakings to conduct their own analysis regarding which SMFs are required. The PRA will assess the appropriateness of these arrangements on a case-by-case basis",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "11.3",
            "summary": "Where a branch operates in the UK alongside a material subsidiary, the PRA expects there to be controls around the division of risks accepted through the subsidiary and the branch (for example, in the",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Whistleblowing",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "12.1",
            "summary": "Third-country branches are required to comply with Rule 2.4 in the Whistleblowing Part of the PRA Rulebook, i",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Re-domiciliation of third-country insurers",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "13.1",
            "summary": "When the third-country branch undertaking that is authorised to operate a third-country branch in the UK redomiciles to another jurisdiction, the PRA expects a new application to be submitted for auth",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Operational risk and outsourcing",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "14.1",
            "summary": "Third-country branches should refer to the following for detailed rules and guidance when considering operational risk management:15",
            "as_at_date": ""
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "14.2",
            "summary": "This section does not consider the requirements and expectations of the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA). The FCA should be contacted directly to understand their requirements and expectations for op",
            "as_at_date": "23/05/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
